Network Device Pattern
  • The Network Device Element (net_device) is used to represent various Network Equipment.
  • This Element's Stereotype extends the UML Device element.
  • The Network Interface Element (net_iface) can be used to represent Logical Interfaces on Device or Server elements.
  • This Element's Stereotype extends the UML Part element.
Network Device Element Tags
  1. Tag Type = Describes type of Network Device (e.g., Load Balancer, Switch)
  2. Tag Summary = A Structured Tag that describes the Device's Vendor and Version. If version is unknown, put spaces or a single period.
Disk Element Tags
  1. Tag type = Defines type of interface (e.g., Primary, VIP, Backup).
  1. Tag name = A Structured Tag that defines the CNAME and IP Address assigned. If IP is unknown, put spaces or a single period.
Constraints
  • Security Devices should use the Appliance or Infrastructure Device type unless it makes more sense to use this element type.
Examples
  • Load Balancer
  • Router
